OL,3,CFamily of Synagogue attack victim
OL,4,Cthank public for 'support and
OL,5,Ccompassion'
OL,7,F"Over the past four weeks we have been
OL,8,Freading and hearing from so many
OL,9,Fpeople across all walks of life as to
OL,10,Fhow Melvin touched their lives through
OL,11,Fhis friendly nature and huge, cheeky
OL,12,Fsmile or some kind words and help that
OL,13,Fchanged their day for the better.
OL,15,F"We are still trying to process the
OL,16,Ftragic and painful events of Yom
OL,17,FKippur at Heaton Park Synagogue. There
OL,18,Fis a space in all of our lives that
OL,19,Fused to be filled by Melvin and we are
OL,20,Fmissing him greatly."
